    Information by Subject
     Environment [menuiconred.gif]
   Research Library
       LIBRARY RESOURCES     REFERENCE
   Electronic Journals
   Database and Indexes
   Book Series

   Acid Rain Program
   Contains Acid Rain laws and regulations; benefits of Acid Rain control;
   and the SO2 Allowance Trading Program.
   Atmospheric Sciences Modeling Division (ASMD)
   Contains information on air pollution and meteorology research.
   Brownfields Initiative
   from EPA.
   Catalog of Known & Putative Nuclear Explosions from Unclassified
   Sources
   Covers over 1900 atmospheric and underground nuclear explosions
   conducted by the U.S., U.K., Russia, France and India. Information
   provided includes latitude, longitude, wave magnitudes and dispersal
   means.
   Ecosystems Research Division - National Exposure Research Laboratory
   (NERL)
   Environmental Professional's Homepage
   Provides a collection of governmental agency offices and their home
   pages.
   National Center for Environmental Research
   Provides information on grants, fellowships and small business research
   awards given by the EPA to collect environmental data for scientific
   research and regulatory decision-making. Also provides results of this
   research.
   Pesticide Regulation Notices
   Policies, procedures and decisions affecting pesticide regulations.
   USGS: The Geology of Radon
   General encyclopedic coverage about radon, its geology and potential;
   links and reading list.
   Water Resources of the United States
   Provides an impressive array of hydrologic data aimed at the scientist.
     DICTIONARIES
   EPA GILS
   Provides access to EPA resources through a Government Information
   Locator Service (GILS).
   Terms of Environment
   Glossary of environmental terms from the EPA.
   Test Method Index (EPA)
   From the EPA, an index of text methods that must be used by US
   environmental laboratories. Indices include keyword, test method and
   document title.
     LANL RESOURCES
   Los Alamos Environmental Technology Publications
   Links to LANL environmental reports and quarterly issues of past
   Site-wide Environmental Impact Statement Employee Information issues.
     LAWS AND TREATIES
   Clean Air Act
   Fulltext of Clean Air Act and 1990 Amendments, from the EPA's Office of
   Air and Radiation.
   Plain English Guide to the Clean Air Act
   With glossary, common air pollutants and more.
   Title VI of the Clean Air Act - Stratospheric Ozone Protection
   Full text of the Clean Air Act-Stratospheric Ozone Protection.
     ELECTRONIC PUBLICATIONS   AGENCIES AND ORGANIZATIONS
   American Water Works Association White Papers
   Papers presented by water supply professionals addressing major issues
   in water supply and public policy debate.
   National Environmental Publications Information--EPA
   Search or browse over 6,000 EPA documents by number or title, National
   Publications Catalog, or Technical Information Packages.
   National Library for the Environment
   Currently includes over 100 fulltext, short Congressional Research
   Service reports on environmental issues. Site will enventually include
   an encyclopedia of environmental topices and in-depth studies on
   specific environmental issues.
   CIESIN (The Consortium for International Earth Science Information
   Network)
   Provides annotated links to educational environmental sources.
   Department of Energy Home Page
   DOE's Office of Environmental Management
   Environmental Protection Agency
   EPA Subsurface Protection and Remediation Division
   Includes information about the Subsurface Remediation Information
   Center and Center for Subsurface Modelling. Supports lists of reports,
   articles and models.
   National Environmental Supercomputing Center
   Resources For The Future
   This non-partisan "think tank"provides information about its
   environmental economics research, and advisory activities on Capitol
   Hill.
   U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission
   Links to information on nuclear reactors, materials and wastes.
   World Energy Efficiency Association (WEEA)
   Institutions from developing and developed countries working on
   increasing energy efficiency.
     REPORTS
   Reports on Federal Agency Major Rules
   General Accounting Office. Bi-monthly update of major rules proposed by
   all federal agencies.
